   {:e #blake3 "fa74edd0335d04aa9fef81f453903445753aaff438b41048276db3e455551c1b" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-c4b070ed; Theory of Mind for LLM Agents; CE-OBSERVE-INSIGHT: The dialogue must be continuous, not periodic. Currently observation and hypothesis generation are DECOUPLED — 21 observations get 21 'recorded +9 datoms' responses with zero contextual insight. Every framework demands continuous dialogue: Freud (superego intervenes at moment of experience), Lacan (signifying chain extends at moment new signifier enters), Vygotsky (scaffolding happens IN the interaction), Popper (contradictions flagged the INSTANT they appear), Bakhtin (meaning co-constructed in utterance-response pair). FIX: Every braid observe returns not just 'recorded' but an IMMEDIATE micro-hypothesis compiled from the newly-connected knowledge state. After recording, the observe pipeline: (1) runs connect_to_existing (CE-CONN), (2) runs detect_topological_event (CE-TOPO) checking for new hubs, contradictions H1, void boundaries H2, (3) if event occurred, runs compile_micro_hypothesis (CE-STEER) generating a one-sentence Socratic question at current temperature, (4) includes micro-hypothesis in the observation response. The micro-hypothesis is recorded in the hypothesis ledger for calibration. This transforms braid from NOTEBOOK (records, 4/10) to SOCRATIC TUTOR (responds, dialogues, scaffolds, challenges, guides, 8+/10). ~60 LOC orchestration in observe pipeline calling functions CE-CONN/TOPO/STEER already define.; Session entity: :task/t-821ca898; Session entity: :recon/trace-d71607645e2553c4; THEORETICAL-SYNTHESIS: Braid through the lens of 9 theoretical frameworks. FREUD: braid is the superego — shapes what enters the ego's consciousness (context window). The daemon's cognitive loop is the superego operating in the preconscious between sessions. LACAN: the datom store is the Symbolic Order. Each observation is a signifier. Connections are the signifying chain. Free energy (1-F(S)) is the gap between Symbolic and Real. Hypothesis phrasing launches a signifying chain through the LLM's unconscious (latent space). CHOMSKY: hypothesis generation is a generative grammar of inquiry — finite rules producing infinite valid hypotheses. CE-STEER's compile function IS the Merge operation. JUNG: temperature schedule traverses archetypes — Fool (high T) -> Hero (medium) -> Shadow (H1 falsification) -> Wise Old Man (low T). Individuation = F(S) convergence. VYGOTSKY: hypotheses must be in the Zone of Proximal Development. Temperature tracks the moving ZPD. The daemon's cognitive loop IS inner speech (compressed, predicative, self-directed thought). POPPER: H1 loop detection IS applying falsifiability criterion to the knowledge graph. KUHN: percolation threshold IS the paradigm shift. LAKATOS: hypothesis ledger's mean prediction error IS progressiveness criterion. DELEUZE: knowledge graph (rhizome) compiled into exploration plans (striated) and back. KANT: LLM provides categories (a priori weights), braid provides intuitions (a posteriori datoms). Neither alone produces knowledge. Together: understanding.; Session entity: :task/t-07a37b9c; Session entity: :recon/trace-c59fb92d4395546a; CE-MIND-INSIGHT: The gap from 8/10 to 10/10 is THEORY OF MIND. Braid currently calibrates to TEMPERATURE (global F(S)) which is a property of the KNOWLEDGE STATE, not the AGENT STATE. Two agents with identical knowledge can be STUCK, LOST, CONFUSED, IN FLOW, or SKIMMING — completely different cognitive states needing different interventions. The agent's cognitive state is OBSERVABLE from data braid already collects: ATTENTION (keyword entropy of recent observations — low entropy = focused, high = scattered), CONFUSION (H1 contradiction density + falling confidence trend), PROGRESS (delta-F(S) per observation), DEPTH (are observations getting more specific over time), ENGAGEMENT (suggestion follow-through rate). Five cognitive modes: LOST (high breadth + low progress -> structural reorientation), STUCK (low breadth + low progress -> lateral escape / basin tunneling), CONFUSED (high contradiction density -> falsification), IN-FLOW (high progress + increasing depth -> minimal intervention or precise deepening), SKIMMING (high breadth + decreasing depth -> challenge depth). Each mode maps to a Jungian archetype: Lost->Wise Old Man, Stuck->Trickster, Confused->Shadow, InFlow->Self, Skimming->Warrior. Each maps to a Vygotskyan ZPD position: Lost=below ZPD (reorient), Stuck=same level different direction, Confused=same level confront, InFlow=in ZPD (advance), Skimming=above ZPD (push harder). Implementation: AgentCognitiveState struct computed from last 10 observations, CognitiveMode enum classified from state signals. ~100 LOC. Integrates into CE-OBSERVE: responsive observation consults agent model before generating micro-hypothesis.\nSession entity: :task/t-3cf81ce2; Responsive Observation — Continuous Socratic Dialogue" :op :assert}
